==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cassation
<hw>Cas*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cassation</ets>. See <er>Cass</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
annulling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A general <qex>cassation</qex> of their constitutions.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Court of cassation</b></col>, <cd>the highest court of
appeal in France, which has power to quash (<itran>Casser</itran>) or
reverse the decisions of the inferior courts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cassava</ent>⟦br⟧
